<HL>
   Business Brief -- United Gaming Inc.:
   Wilms to Pay $10 Million
   To Lift His Stake to 59%
</HL>
<DATE>
05/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   UGAM
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   United Gaming Inc. said it reached an agreement in
principle under which Alfred H. Wilms, chairman, will buy an
additional $10 million of the company's common stock.
   Mr. Wilms now owns 3,732,091 United Gaming common shares,
or about 47% of its stock outstanding. The additional
investment, which is subject to several conditions including
board approval, would boost his stake approximately 12%, to
about 59% of the company's shares.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Based in Las Vegas, Nev., United Gaming operates gambling
machine routes and sells gambling equipment.
   David Scheinman, president, said the investment would give
the company capital to fund its entry into the casino hotel
business and is Mr. Wilms's vote of confidence in the
company's future.
</TEXT>
